\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 Introduction to Philosophy
\f1\b0\fs24 \
\pard\pardeftab720\qc\partightenfactor0

\f2\i\fs28 \cf0 By J.T. James
\f1\i0\fs24 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f3\fs29\fsmilli14667 \cf0 \strokec2 \uc0\u8232 	Traditionally introductions to subjects focus on the history of the field, evolution of ideas, and people that contributed to them, while often being too specific or too broad with the information presented. This neglects the fundamentals, the most valuable ideas, and the unsolved problems get insufficient focus. \u8232 
\f1\fs24 \
\pard\pardeftab720\fi960\partightenfactor0

\f3\fs29\fsmilli14667 \cf0 \strokec2 Highest value ideas: Value in exploring the truths of existence - creating a value in discovery, acceptance of ignorance, tools discovering truths, and considering how we should all live together.\'a0
\f1\fs24 \

\f3\fs29\fsmilli14667 I think if we just walk people through the high value questions and ideas can create and can easily inspire self-discovery of further ideas, or the sources of them. Today\'92s technology no longer requires us to slog through rote memorization of history as reference materials never far from our fingertips.\'a0
\f1\fs24 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf0 \strokec2 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs29\fsmilli14667 \cf0 \strokec2 Introduction to Philosophy
\f1\b0\fs24 \strokec2 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f3\fs29\fsmilli14667 \cf0 Philosophy is the study of fundamental questions about existence. \uc0\u8232 Seeking answers to 3 main areas: \u8232 What is Reality and how does it work?\u8232 How do we refine our Reasoning to better find truth?\u8232 What is the Right way to live, what are our goals, and what is the best way to achieve them? \u8232 \u8232 \cf3 \strokec3 Physics 
\fs26\fsmilli13333 \cf4 \strokec4 \uc0\u9702 
\fs29\fsmilli14667 \cf0 \strokec2 \uc0\u8232 \cf5 \strokec5 Reason 
\fs26\fsmilli13333 \'95
\fs29\fsmilli14667 \cf0 \strokec2 \uc0\u8232 \cf6 \strokec6 Ethics 
\fs26\fsmilli13333 \cf4 \strokec4 \uc0\u8227 
\fs29\fsmilli14667 \cf0 \strokec2 \uc0\u8232 \cf3 \strokec3 Questions like: \uc0\u8232 \u9702  Why is there something rather than nothing?\u8232  \'a0 - How does existence function?\u8232  \'a0 - What is life?
\f1\fs24 \cf0 \strokec2 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f3\fs29\fsmilli14667 \cf3 \strokec3 \'a0\'a0\'a0-\'a0\'a0
\f1\fs24 \cf0 \strokec2 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f3\fs29\fsmilli14667 \cf5 \strokec5 \'95 How do we come to know?\uc0\u8232  \'a0 - What is knowledge anyway?\cf3 \strokec3 \uc0\u8232 \cf6 \strokec6 \uc0\u8227  Why are we here?\u8232  \'a0 - What is our purpose?\u8232 \u8227  How should we structure society to fulfill a general purpose?\cf3 \strokec3 \uc0\u8232 
\f1\fs24 \cf0 \strokec2 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f3\fs29\fsmilli14667 \cf0 We don\'92t have answers to these questions or even much simpler ones. So how do we start to answer these questions?\uc0\u8232 \u8232 Over time various ideologies have been created to try and provide these answers. \u8232 \u8232 Humanism is generally the one we would call the most advanced, informed by science\u8232 \u8232 Rationality or Reason became our methods for trying to solve questions around how to get answers. Logic, empiricism, \u8232 \u8232 The sciences starting with natural philosophy (or now physics) became \cf3 \strokec3 \uc0\u8232 \cf0 \strokec2 Striving to answer these questions and the many that follow is the \'91first order values\'92 of Philosophy and all the societies birthed from it, from the Greeks to the United States of America.\uc0\u8232 \u8232 Various times throughout history societies have worked to answer these questions, and at least 2,500 years later we don\'92t have good answers. These are hard questions to answer and many of us are still trying to. \u8232 \u8232 Recognizing and then accepting our ignorance is something we generally ascribe to be a fundamental basis of wisdom. \u8232 \u8232 [See Plato\'92s Apology]\u8232 \u8232 \u8232 \u8232 Accurately assessing how much we know and how well we think gives us the ability to effectively think about how to broaden our knowledge. \u8232 \u8232 Our wisdom is limited by our ability to accurately assess our knowledge. \u8232 \u8232 \u8232 \u8232 For those who value these questions and the culture and progress that has come from them striving to continue the work of answering them in part answers our purpose. To recognize our ignorance\u8232 \u8232 \u8232 or many who follow the Western Traditions of Philosophy e\'92ve made good headway on a variety of these questions but none of them are fully answered. We are still too ignorant of the nature of existence (including ourselves), the most effective ways to discover truths, and we still disagree on various aspects of our purpose and how to structure society to achieve a purpose even when there is alignment there. \u8232 \u8232 The fundamentals of a field studying fundamental questions relate to \u8232 
\f1\fs24 \

\f3\fs29\fsmilli14667 We don\'92t have answers to these questions or even much simpler ones. So how do we start to answer these questions?\uc0\u8232 
\f1\fs24 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs29\fsmilli14667 \cf0 \strokec2 Question: What is the prime question?
\f1\b0\fs24 \strokec2 \
\pard\pardeftab720\li960\fi-960\partightenfactor0

\f3\fs29\fsmilli14667 \cf0 \ul \ulc0 \strokec2 Answer\ulnone : Where did we come from, why are we here, what\'92s our purpose, what\'92s our meaning, etc?
\f1\fs24 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf0 \strokec2 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs29\fsmilli14667 \cf0 \strokec2 Question: What\'92s the answer?
\f1\b0\fs24 \strokec2 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f3\fs29\fsmilli14667 \cf0 	\ul \strokec2 Answer\ulnone \strokec2 : We don\'92t know\'a0
\f1\fs24 \
\
\pard\pardeftab720\li960\fi-960\partightenfactor0

\f2\i\fs26\fsmilli13333 \cf0 \strokec2 Point out how important that answer is. How we need to accept that answer as valid. It is the impetus. It is the motivation of a everything that follows, discovery is the motive of philosophy.
\f1\i0\fs24 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf0 \strokec2 \
\pard\pardeftab720\li960\fi-960\partightenfactor0

\f2\i\fs26\fsmilli13333 \cf0 \strokec2 An answer of ignorance should be met by valuing the wisdom instead of shaming the \'91stupidity\'92 of the answerer.\'a0
\f1\i0\fs24 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf0 \strokec2 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs29\fsmilli14667 \cf0 \strokec2 Question: So...how do we come to know?
\f1\b0\fs24 \strokec2 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f2\i\fs29\fsmilli14667 \cf0 \strokec2 \'a0	
\f3\i0 \ul Answer\ulnone \strokec2 : Reason and then the scientific method.
\f1\fs24 \
\
\pard\pardeftab720\li960\fi-960\partightenfactor0

\f2\i\fs26\fsmilli13333 \cf0 \strokec2 I assume the student already has at least passing familiar with science. However, most people college educated and beyond seem to have very little understanding of what reason actually is.\'a0
\f1\i0\fs24 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf0 \strokec2 \
\pard\pardeftab720\li960\fi-960\partightenfactor0

\f2\i\fs26\fsmilli13333 \cf0 \strokec2 A incomplete but simple definition of reason is simply logic. By logic we mean the process of understanding the relationship between ideas and facts, and sometimes finding new facts or even inventions from those relationships.\'a0
\f1\i0\fs24 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf0 \strokec2 \
\pard\pardeftab720\li960\fi-960\partightenfactor0

\f2\i\fs26\fsmilli13333 \cf0 \strokec2 It might be worth mentioning that the scientific method is somewhat living. It has developed over time and may continue to develop.
\f1\i0\fs24 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf0 \strokec2 \
\pard\pardeftab720\li960\fi-960\partightenfactor0

\f2\i\fs26\fsmilli13333 \cf0 \strokec2 This introduction course would spin off into a course more formally on reason and on the philosophy of science or generally epistemology.\'a0
\f1\i0\fs24 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf0 \strokec2 \
\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs29\fsmilli14667 \cf0 \strokec2 Abstractly accurate useful fiction on the history of philosophy from there:\'a0
\f1\b0\fs24 \strokec2 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f3\fs29\fsmilli14667 \cf0 \'95 We tasked some of our philosophers with observing what happens around us, we call them natural scientists and philosophers, and they have various fields they divide themselves further into.\'a0
\f1\fs24 \
\

\f3\fs29\fsmilli14667 \'95 We tasked another group to work with them and think through the relationship of the observations, we call them epistemologist, and have a specificialization relating to the philosophy of science.\'a0
\f1\fs24 \
\

\f3\fs29\fsmilli14667 \'95 Not long after the natural scientists set out to do their task it became clear that science and epistemology are hard and going to take a long time. Understanding the forces of nature will also require of us to create a stable society that encourages and invests in discovery.
\f1\fs24 \
\

\f3\fs29\fsmilli14667 \'95 This new task requires us to think about an additional area of existence, structuring society. The social sciences and humanities work to help us better understand how to structure society and help us enjoy our time while alive (improve human well-being). Enjoyment of our time is also highly related to societal stability.\'a0
\f1\fs24 \
\
\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs29\fsmilli14667 \cf0 \strokec2 An early idea of how to structure society
\f1\b0\fs24 \strokec2 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f3\fs29\fsmilli14667 \cf0 The Republic
\f1\fs24 \

\f3\fs29\fsmilli14667 Old philosophers noticed that we aren\'92t all equal. Some of us are better at some things than others and as such suggested:
\f1\fs24 \

\f3\fs29\fsmilli14667 \'95 Those of us who are the most just, wise, and suited for reason should lead society
\f1\fs24 \

\f3\fs29\fsmilli14667 \'95 Those of us the more martially inclined should protect society and maintain its order
\f1\fs24 \

\f3\fs29\fsmilli14667 \'95 The rest of us should labor to produce for society	
\f1\fs24 \
\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs29\fsmilli14667 \cf0 \strokec2 Sorting Problem
\f1\b0\fs24 \strokec2 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f3\fs29\fsmilli14667 \cf0 We\'92ve come to learn that there are many problems with this idea, but one of the more significant is that we are really bad at recognizing and sorting people based on their talents, potential, and likelihood of being a just and wise person.
\f1\fs24 \
\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs29\fsmilli14667 \cf0 \strokec2 Capitalism and Democracy as an answer to the sorting problem
\f1\b0\fs24 \strokec2 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f3\fs29\fsmilli14667 \cf0 We are currently so bad at sorting people we\'92ve decided to structure our society to enable people to sort themselves.The current general idea is to strive to build a world with equal opportunity and leave the sorting to the seemingly naturally progressive forces of the market and opinions democratic citizen.\'a0
\f1\fs24 \
\

